<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 18 at 2:15AM PST  by NWS Reno</headline>
<description>...Areas of Freezing Fog in Western Nevada...
Freezing fog is migrating around the Basin and Range, so be
diligent of rapid changing conditions if you`re driving before
sunrise this morning.
Visibility down to one quarter mile in freezing fog for portions
of Interstate 80 between Fernley-Lovelock-Winnemucca, Highway 95
near Schurz-Fallon, and Highway 50 between Carson City and
Fallon. There is also a pocket of freezing fog in the vicinity of
Yerington early this morning.
Be prepared for localized hazardous driving conditions due to low
visibility and the potential for frosty, slick conditions. Slow
down and leave plenty of distance ahead of you.</description>
